    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-05-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="531"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName type="from">Jonkheer R. de Marees van Swinderen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: The royal legation has not
                    failed to forward to the Government of the Queen the memorandum relating to the
                    Japanese declaration about the sale of coal during the actual war in the far
                    Orient which accompanied the note which your excellency kindly addressed to it
                    on February 16 last.</p>
                <p>I have been instructed to transmit to the Government of the United States the
                    thanks of the Royal Government for the memorandum of which it has taken notice
                    with great interest and in which it fully concurs.</p>
                <p>I take this occasion, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Van Swinderen.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
